loading data

library(datasets)
titanic=read.csv("/Users/tuzigudong/Desktop/data/train.csv")

Dealing with missing values

miss_val <- sapply(titanic, function(x) sum(is.na(x)))
perct_miss <- as.data.frame(round((miss_val/nrow(titanic))*100,1))

replacing missing values using average value

summary(titanic$Age)
##    Min. 1st Qu.  Median    Mean 3rd Qu.    Max.    NA's 
##    0.42   20.12   28.00   29.70   38.00   80.00     177
average_age <- mean(titanic$Age,trim=0,na.rm=TRUE)
titanic$Age[is.na(titanic$Age)]<-average_age
titanic$Age<-as.integer(titanic$Age)
summary(titanic$Age)
##    Min. 1st Qu.  Median    Mean 3rd Qu.    Max. 
##    0.00   22.00   29.00   29.54   35.00   80.00

standard the data factor

titanic$Survived<-factor(titanic$Survived,levels=c(0,1))
titanic$SibSp<-factor(titanic$SibSp)
titanic$Parch<-factor(titanic$Parch)
titanic$Pclass<-factor(titanic$Pclass)

draw whister-plot

boxplot(titanic$Age~titanic$Survived,data=titanic,yslim=c(0,100),las=1,ylab="Age",xlab="survived")

boxplot(titanic$Fare~titanic$Survived,data=titanic,ylab="Fare",xlab="survived")

draw heatmaps

Because there are too many data, we select the first 20 row of them to draw the heat maps

titanic<-titanic[1:20,]
row.names(titanic)<-titanic$Name
titanic_matrix<-data.matrix(titanic)
titanic_heatmap<-heatmap(titanic_matrix,Rowv=NA,Colv=NA,col=cm.colors(256),scale="column",margins=c(5,10))
